President Donald J. Trump met with Mayor Rudy Giuliani, General Keith Alexander, Thomas P. Bossert, and energy sector leaders to discuss energy sector resilience and cybersecurity. They discussed the unique challenges the sector faces and strategic initiatives to address malicious cyber activity. President Trump emphasized the importance of a continuing public and private partnership to combat threats against the energy sector, particularly the power grid. He expressed his commitment to enhancing electric grid security and resilience, citing his Executive Order on strengthening cybersecurity. The President also emphasized the need to work closely with infrastructure providers and improve the existing public and private partnership framework for effective risk management.